definition.value: An organic radical generated from urate.
A primary nitroalkane that is heptane substituted by a nitro group at position 1.
An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is decanedioic (sebacic) acid carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 3.
A primary nitroalkane that is hexane substituted by a nitro group at position 1.
A member of the class of phenols carrying two tert-butyl substituents at positions 2 and 4.
A member of the class of furans that is furan in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a pentyl group. It is found in many heat-processed foods and drinks.
A fatty acid methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of tetradecanoic acid (myristic acid) with methanol.
